<p style="text-align: center">
<span class="PRTitle"><!-- NewsTitle.start -->Transcript of Interview of Senate President Juan Ponce Enrile<!-- NewsTitle.end --></span>
</p>
<!-- NewsBody.start --><p style="text-align: justify">On the new AFP Chief Oban</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Reaction n'yo po sa pagkaka-appoint ni General Oban?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: Hindi ko masyado kilala si Oban pero balita ko mahusay  na opisyal.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Pero hanggang nine months lang daw po ang itatagal ng appointment nya, sir?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: It doesn't matter. He was appointed by the President. That's the prerogative of the President as Commander-in-Chief.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: You think, sir, magagawa niya po 'yung mga reforms na...</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: He can do what he can do. You can't expect him to do miracles in nine months. The AFP is too big in terms of equipment, training, modernization, and so forth.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, how about 'yung fixed term po ng AFP Chief-of-Staff? Ano po ang status sa Senate?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: I'm against it. Why should we put a fixed term? If he has a fixed term, he might get a stupid Chief-of-Staff who will defy his Commander-in-Chief. Do you want that? He will tell the Commander-in-Chief, "Go ahead and do it yourself," if you give him a fixed term. A Commander must be able to kick out any subordinate at any time when there is a reason for it. He is no Commander if he cannot do that.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">On the Impeachment Case of the Ombudsman</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, just in case, should the House transmit the articles of impeachment against Gutierrez, would the Senate adopt the same impeachment rules adopted during the Estrada hearing?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: We will have to review the rules.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, according to Ombudsman Gutierrez, may tiwala siya sa Senate. Mas dito raw siya haharap kapag naiakyat dito ang impeachment.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: We will do what we have to do as Senators of the Republic under our oath to do justice to people who come to us.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, ina-assure n'yo na magiging impartial?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: I don't have to assure her. That's my oath. And I'm not going to be a party to just do harm to somebody if she is innocent. If she is guilty, then so be it. That's my concept of justice.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">On the International Criminal Court</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: Sir, what is the Rome Statute on the International Criminal Court?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: I have asked a lot of questions from the President when I met him and I have to study it very carefully.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">Q: So, wala pa kayong stand, sir, kung dapat na i-ratify na?</p>
<p style="text-align: justify">SP: Wala pa akong stand. I'm going to ask a lot of questions.</p>
